<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-14618 AND RTLO-16618
        SERIES - DISASSEMBLE - AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="3">
        <title>AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring from the hub of the front auxiliary drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13019b9">Figure 119</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13019b9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13019b9" filename="../figg13/G13019b9.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 119. Remove Snap Ring From Hub of Front Auxiliary Drive Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using the rear face of the retainer ring as a base, press the drive gear through the bearing
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13019c0">Figure 120</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13019c0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13019c0" filename="../figg13/G13019c0.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 120. Press Drive Gear Through Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If necessary, remove the O-rings from the hub O.D. of the front auxiliary drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13019c1">Figure 121</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13019c1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13019c1" filename="../figg13/G13019c1.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 121. Remove O-Rings From Hub O.D. of Front Auxiliary Drive Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
